,Recommended,428900,25765607,"Posted: 29 September, 2016",all,RipWitch,"""Linea, the Game"" is a cheap, platform dodging game including 4 levels the get increasingly difficult and the only thing distracting you will be the urge to look at the clock. Each level is somewhat randomly generated and the quota for finishing a level is surviving for 60 seconds. While each replay of a level is random, each does contain patterns that constantly show up to allow you to learn through trail and error to pass as those are usually ones that causes a game over.Despite the difficulty increase, each level is possible through constant replaying, and with this often comes the feelings of excitement as you pass your last high score/ beat the level, despair when you are 1 second away, or determination while playing.It does not show that it is controller supported, but it is and I do recommend playing with a controller. It makes it easier and faster to dodge and doesn't wear on the fingers like playing with the keyboard does.I also do recommend looking at the achievements, as one requires you to play the first level without doing the tutorial first (locking you out from the achievement if you play the tutorial first). The dev has added a launch option to reset by demand (however this resets everything in the process).Overall, I recommend this game, but be warned this game is harder than it looks like and be ready to die a lot."
