,Recommended,428900,23019786,"Posted: 16 May, 2016",all,Joshyy,"Linea, the Game is a minimalistic dodging action game akin to Super Hexagon. The premise of the gameplay comes from a series of red bars that move towards your screen, normally in one of the 4 directional positions (up, down, left, right). The object of the game is to dodge these red bars and survive for as long as possible. (60 seconds minimum to progress to the next level.) The gameplay is supplemented with minimialistic white and gray backgrounds, and fast-paced chiptune music.Each stage has its own music track, so repetitive plays on the same level can cause the music to grow stale. The patterns for which objects appear don't seem too varied, so they become easier to pick up as the stage is repeated.The difficulty ramps up as you progress through stages; the first few levels are relatively drawn out, enabling an understanding of the mechanics of the game. Once the player reaches stages 3 and 4, the tempo and difficulty increases. There is also currently a DLC pack with 3 extra stages and a bonus coin collecting stage, also with increasing the difficulty from the last stage of the game.Overall, I was able to complete the game in one sitting. Replayability seems low, as the stages don't seem to increase in difficulty regardless of time. Those that are quite fond of these types of games are likely to have short play times as well, while newer members might find a challenge with the later stages. I was able to pick up both the game and DLC for 2 dollars, and received 1.5 hours of play time.Will recommend for the low price of the bundle coupled with the quality of the game."
