76561198355896078,Recommended,428900,34482936,Posted: 25 August,all,Axarional,"6/10it's a nice challenge for those who like fast-paced, reaction-based games and note that this is NOT for those looking for a casual game on the couch.I personally didn't mind the music despite being a metal fan, although i'm sure others will have their varying opinions on the music so i can't say that the music is bad/good.Gameplay was interesting when there was a different, given way to beat the level however overall i think the Dev should have given the player some sort of marker, like in the tutorial, showing them what space they occupy as it makes the core mechanic of the game, dodging, unnecessarily more difficult.Finally, while i did somewhat enjoy the game:TO THE DEVplease remove or at least, change the achievement where you had to play the first level instead of the tutorial. This is because after the player finishes the tutorial, they have to reset what they had done so far which is made only more painful since they don't know how to reset the game and/or find your guide on resetting which is located in the game forum. THIS SHOULD NOT HAPPEN."
