,Recommended,428900,32758194,Posted: 24 June,all,Drizzle,"This is a basic reaction speed game where you use the four arrow keys (or wasd) to pilot yourself and dodge red beams. It's pretty fun, but if you're really good at such games, you'll blow away the 4 levels in no time.Wait... 4 levels? Yes, 4 levels. It has another DLC that adds 4 more levels for you. Buying the bundle costs a bit over 2 dollars. Do the math and that comes to 25 cents per level.All of these 8 levels are quite hard to the average player and can (and will) chip away at your time. It takes a bit of practice to get the hang of, but the feeling you get after beating one level is (sometimes) worth it.Is the game worth it? Well... that's debatable. If you're interested in such a game, go for it. Otherwise, try spending your money on something else that suites your liking."
